Interface KeyValueIterator<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - Type of keys
    V - Type of values
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, java.io.Closeable, java.util.Iterator<KeyValue<K,V>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    WindowStoreIterator<V>

    public interface KeyValueIterator<K,V>
extends java.util.Iterator<KeyValue<K,V>>, java.io.Closeable
    Iterator interface of KeyValue. Users must call its close method explicitly upon completeness to release resources, or use try-with-resources statement (available since JDK7) for this Closeable class.
